<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="37">
In Peru, 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Rchb. f., Linnaea" authorityYear="1876" class="Actinopterygii" family="Liparidae" genus="Liparis" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Liparis brachystalix" order="Scorpaeniformes" pageId="0" pageNumber="37" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="brachystalix">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="37">Liparis brachystalix</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
was collected in the 1960s in the cloud forests of Amazonas, but it was overlooked (Brako and Zarucchi 2993; 
<bibRefCitation DOI="https://doi.org/10.5962/bhl.title.63538" author="Ulloa Ulloa, C" journalOrPublisher="Botany" pageId="0" pageNumber="37" refId="B21" refString="Ulloa Ulloa, C, Zarucchi, JL, Leon, B, 2004. Diez anos de adiciones a la flora del Peru. Arnaldoa (edicion especial): 7-242. https://doi.org/10.5962/bhl.title.63538" title="Diez anos de adiciones a la flora del Peru. Arnaldoa (edicion especial): 7 - 242." url="https://doi.org/10.5962/bhl.title.63538" year="2004">Ulloa Ulloa et al. 2004</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation DOI="https://doi.org/10.1126/science.aao0398" author="Ulloa Ulloa, C" journalOrPublisher="Science" pageId="0" pageNumber="37" pagination="1614 - 1617" refId="B22" refString="Ulloa Ulloa, C, Acevedo-Rodriguez, P, Beck, S, Belgrano, MJ, Bernal, R, Berry, PE, Brako, L, Celis, M, Davidse, G, Forzza, RC, Gradstein, SR, Hokche, O, Leon, B, Leon-Yanez, S, Magill, RE, Neill, DA, Nee, M, Raven, PH, Stimme, H, Strong, MT, Villasenor, JL, Zarucchi, JL, Zuloaga, FO, Jorgensen, PM, 2017. An integrated assessment of the vascular plant species of the Americas. Science 358 (6370): 1614 - 1617, DOI: https://doi.org/10.1126/science.aao0398" title="An integrated assessment of the vascular plant species of the Americas." url="https://doi.org/10.1126/science.aao0398" volume="358" year="2017">2017</bibRefCitation>
). In a recent update of the checklist of Peruvian orchids of 
<bibRefCitation author="Zelenko, H" journalOrPublisher="Science" pageId="0" pageNumber="37" refId="B23" refString="Zelenko, H, Bermudez, P, 2009. Orchid Species of Peru. Zai Publications. Quito, 407 pp." title="Orchid Species of Peru. Zai Publications. Quito, 407 pp." year="2009">Zelenko and Bermudez (2009)</bibRefCitation>
published by 
<bibRefCitation author="Goicochea, A" journalOrPublisher="Harvard Papers in Botany" pageId="0" pageNumber="37" refId="B11" refString="Goicochea, A, Gutierrez, A, Ruiz, A, Salas, M, 2019. Orquideas de Peru: Relacion de Especies y sus Sinonimos. G&amp;G Corporation S.A.C., 288 pp." title="Orquideas de Peru: Relacion de Especies y sus Sinonimos. G &amp; G Corporation S. A. C., 288 pp." year="2019">Goicochea et. al. (2019)</bibRefCitation>
, 
<taxonomicName genus="L." lsidName="L. brachystalix" pageId="0" pageNumber="37" rank="species" species="brachystalix">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="37">L. brachystalix</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
was recorded for the first time in Peru. However, the record by 
<bibRefCitation author="Goicochea, A" journalOrPublisher="Harvard Papers in Botany" pageId="0" pageNumber="37" refId="B11" refString="Goicochea, A, Gutierrez, A, Ruiz, A, Salas, M, 2019. Orquideas de Peru: Relacion de Especies y sus Sinonimos. G&amp;G Corporation S.A.C., 288 pp." title="Orquideas de Peru: Relacion de Especies y sus Sinonimos. G &amp; G Corporation S. A. C., 288 pp." year="2019">Goicochea et al. (2019)</bibRefCitation>
did not indicate any vouchers supporting it. Therefore, herein we provide the first vouchered citation of 
<taxonomicName genus="L." lsidName="L. brachystalix" pageId="0" pageNumber="37" rank="species" species="brachystalix">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="37">L. brachystalix</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
for this country. 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Rchb. f., Linnaea" authorityYear="1876" class="Actinopterygii" family="Liparidae" genus="Liparis" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Liparis brachystalix" order="Scorpaeniformes" pageId="0" pageNumber="37" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="brachystalix">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="37">Liparis brachystalix</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is widespread along the eastern slope of the Peruvian Andes, inhabiting the cloud forest of Amazonas, Pasco, and Huancavelica at an altitude of 2000-2900 m.
</paragraph>
